      "writtenOn": "2026-02-17T20:38:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The purpose of this struct is to configure which properties are monitored.\n\nThe default value for all of the struct fields is \"false\", meaning that property not monitored.\n\nIf you try to get the value of an unmonitored property, some return a logical default and others throw an exception. See the doxygen for details. But you aren\u0027t getting the real value for any of the properties if monitoring is not enabled.\n\nIn your case, I think you want to turn on all monitoring. Set all struct fields to true.",
      "revId": "22023a1791809e4f827e7ff50aa38aa4179dfe89",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
